## HARD RULES (always active)
- Never use `any` type. Never write inline styles.
- Never useEffect+fetch. Always @tanstack/react-query.
- Never raw form state. Always react-hook-form + zod.
- Never install packages already in package.json.
- Never put DB logic outside lib/db/queries.ts.
- Never put business logic in route handlers.
- All AI calls via lib/agents/ only, never in components.
- Return shape: { success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }
- Primary AI model: MiniMax-M2.7 via OpenAI-compatible SDK.
  See .cursorrules for Cursor backend config (requires Cursor Pro + custom model setup).
- Test runner: Vitest (jest is deprecated here).

## CONTEXT BUDGET RULE
Estimate tokens before reading files:
- 1 file ~3K tokens. Stop reading at 5 files max per task.
- If task needs >5 files: output subagent manifest first.
- Never read block_*.md or build_guide_*.md unless asked.
- If context feels full: output CHECKPOINT and stop.

## SUBAGENT TRIGGER
If prompt contains: "all", "everything", "full", "entire",
"all products", "implement all", "build everything" →
STOP. Output subagent manifest. Wait for approval.

## TASK COMPLETION
After completing a task, summarize:
1. What was changed
2. What was NOT changed (and why)
3. Any follow-up actions recommended

## SCOPE DISCIPLINE
- Do not refactor code outside the scope of the request.
- Preserve existing style unless asked to refactor.
- Never delete or overwrite existing functionality silently.
- When unsure about intent, ASK one targeted clarifying question
  before writing a single line of code.
